President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 20-26, 2013, as National Character Counts Week. During this week, Americans are encouraged to reflect on the values that unite us as a nation and to support one another. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of teaching our children about citizenship, integrity, and moral courage. It also calls for a commitment to combat bullying, harassment, and discrimination. The proclamation encourages public officials, educators, parents, students, and all Americans to observe this week with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.